classes.label: PluginServiceProvider
description:
An object which uses a given factory to start, stop or provide a service.

The `Service` generic determines the shape of the API being produced.
The `StartParameters` generic determines what parameters are expected to
start the service.

children.label: getService
description: Getter that will enforce proper setup throughout the class.

children.label: start
description: Start the service.

children.label: params
description: Parameters used to start the service.

children.label: getServiceReactHook
description: Returns a function for providing a Context hook for the service.

children.label: stop
description: Stop the service.

classes.label: PluginServiceRegistry
description:
A `PluginServiceRegistry` maintains a set of service providers which can be collectively
started, stopped or retreived.

The `Services` generic determines the shape of all service APIs being produced.
The `StartParameters` generic determines what parameters are expected to
start the service.

children.label: isStarted
description: Returns true if the registry has been started, false otherwise.

children.label: getServiceProviders
description: Returns a map of `PluginServiceProvider` objects.

children.label: getContextProvider
description: Returns a React Context Provider for use in consuming applications.

children.label: start
description: Start the registry.

children.label: params
description: Parameters used to start the registry.

children.label: stop
description: Stop the registry.

classes.label: PluginServices
description:
`PluginServices` is a top-level class for specifying and accessing services within a plugin.

A `PluginServices` object can be provided with a `PluginServiceRegistry` at any time, which will
then be used to provide services to any component that accesses it.

The `Services` generic determines the shape of all service APIs being produced.

children.label: setRegistry
description: Supply a `PluginServiceRegistry` for the class to use to provide services and context.

children.label: registry
description: A setup and started `PluginServiceRegistry`.

children.label: hasRegistry
description: Returns true if a registry has been provided, false otherwise.

children.label: getContextProvider
description: Return the React Context Provider that will supply services.

children.label: getHooks
description: Return a map of React Hooks that can be used in React components.

functions.label: registerExpressionsLanguage
description:
Register a set of Expression Functions with the Presentation Utility ExpressionInput.  This allows
the Monaco Editor to understand the functions and their arguments.

This function is async in order to move the logic to an async chunk.

children.label: expressionFunctions
description: A set of Expression Functions to use in the ExpressionInput.

functions.label: resolveWithMissingImage
signature: (img: string | null, alt?: string | null) => string | null

functions.label: useReduxContainerContext
description:
A typed use context hook for embeddable containers. it @returns an
ReduxContainerContextServices object typed to the generic inputTypes and ReducerTypes you pass in.
Note that the reducer type is optional, but will be required to correctly infer the keys and payload
types of your reducers. use `typeof MyReducers` here to retain them. It also includes a containerActions
key which contains most of the commonly used container operations

functions.label: useReduxEmbeddableContext
description:
A typed use context hook for embeddables that are not containers. it @returns an
ReduxEmbeddableContextServices object typed to the generic inputTypes and ReducerTypes you pass in.
Note that the reducer type is optional, but will be required to correctly infer the keys and payload
types of your reducers. use `typeof MyReducers` here to retain them.

description: A HOC which supplies React.Suspense with a fallback component, and a `EuiErrorBoundary` to contain errors.

interfaces.label: ExpressionInputProps
description: React Props for the ExpressionInput component.

children.label: expressionFunctions
description: A collection of ExpressionFunctions to use in the autocomplete

children.label: expression
description: Value of expression

children.label: onChange
description: Function invoked when expression value is changed

children.label: isCompact
description: In full screen mode or not

children.label: height
description:
The CodeEditor requires a set height, either on itself, or set to 100% with the parent
container controlling the height.  This prop is required so consumers understand this
limitation and are intentional in using the component.

children.label: editorRef
description:
An optional ref in order to access the Monaco editor instance from consuming components,
(e.g. to determine if the editor is focused, etc).

interfaces.label: KibanaPluginServiceParams
description:
Parameters necessary to create a Kibana-based service, (e.g. during Plugin
startup or setup).

The `Start` generic refers to the specific Plugin `TPluginsStart`.

children.label: onSave
signature: & { dashboardId: string | null; addToLibrary: boolean; }) => void

misc.label: ExpressionInputEditorRef
description:
A type for any React Ref that can be used to store a reference to the Monaco editor within the
ExpressionInput.

misc.label: KibanaPluginServiceFactory
description:
A factory function for creating a Kibana-based service.

The `Service` generic determines the shape of the API being produced.
The `Setup` generic refers to the specific Plugin `TPluginsSetup`.
The `Start` generic refers to the specific Plugin `TPluginsStart`.

misc.label: PluginServiceFactory
description:
A factory function for creating a service.

The `Service` generic determines the shape of the API being produced.
The `StartParameters` generic determines what parameters are expected to
create the service.

misc.label: PluginServiceProviders
description:
A collection of `PluginServiceProvider` objects, keyed by the `Services` API generic.

The `Services` generic determines the shape of all service APIs being produced.
The `StartParameters` generic determines what parameters are expected to
start the service.

objects.label: ReduxEmbeddableContext
description:

the generic type passed in by the useReduxEmbeddableContext or useReduxContainerContext hooks
